nvas = document.createElement('canvas'); canvas.width = width; canvas.height = height; document.body.appendChild(canvas); //Scene const scene = new THREE.Scene(); const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(45, width / height, 0.1, 1000); scene.add(camera); //Meshes const sphereGeometry = new THREE.SphereGeometry(2, 64, 64); const sphereMaterial = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial({color: 0xfffaaa}); const sphere = new THREE.Mesh(sphereGeometry, sphereMaterial); scene.add(sphere); //Renderer const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({canvas}); renderer.setSize(width, height); document.body.appendChild(renderer.domElement); renderer.render(scene, camera); Обратите внимание, что я также поменял аспект камеры на (width / height) вместо просто width как было раньше."},{"instruction":"as a programmer with php and python how to make a mobile website that makes camera on phone scans Qr code and response with Ar games","output":"To create a mobile website that allows users to scan QR codes and play AR games, follow these steps: 1. Choose a framework to build your mobile website. You can use frameworks like React Native, Ionic, or AngularJS for building cross-platform mobile applications. 2. Use a QR code scanning library like ZXing or QuaggaJS to detect and decode QR codes using the camera of the user's mobile device. 3. Integrate a web-based AR game engine like AR.js or A-Frame to render AR content on the user's mobile device. 4. Use PHP/Python as a backend for storing and retrieving user data such as game scores, achievements, and user profiles. 5. Implement a database to store user's data and also AR content. 6. Use push notifications to update users with new games or rewards. 7. Test and debug your mobile website on various devices to ensure compatibility and functionality. By following these steps, you can create an innovative mobile website that utilizes the power of PHP and Python to create a unique user experience."},{"instruction":"Prépare moi un discours de jumelage avec 